3. <Assumption Ledger>

  <A1 status="safe">
    <writing> fixes <the-said>, not the living <speech-event>.
  </A1>

  <A2 status="safe">
    <social-action> becomes interpretable when it leaves a <trace>.
  </A2>

  <A3 status="safe">
    <trace> is the bridge between <Ricoeurian-text> and <human-science-object>.
  </A3>

  <A4 status="safe">
    <authorial-intention> and <agent-intention> matter, but they do not govern final meaning.
  </A4>

  <A5 status="safe">
    <interpretation> requires both <guessing> and <validation>.
  </A5>

  <A6 status="safe">
    <AI-artifacts>, <bureaucratic-records>, and <digital-logs> are contemporary forms of <inscribed-action>.
  </A6>

  <A7 status="uncertain">
    The eventual program may become a writing method, classroom model, critique engine, annotation system, or software tool.
  </A7>

  <A8 status="requires-user-decision">
