8. <Program Text>

  PROGRAM <HermeneuticTraceInterpreter>

    INPUT:
      <TraceInput>

    OUTPUT:
      <HermeneuticReport>

    STEP 1: [classify-input
]
      IF <artifact_or_action> is spoken discourse:
        SET <type> = <SpeechEvent>
      ELSE IF <artifact_or_action> is written language:
        SET <type> = <Text>
      ELSE IF <artifact_or_action> is human deed:
        SET <type> = <MeaningfulAction>
      ELSE IF <artifact_or_action> is model-generated media:
        SET <type> = <AIArtifact>
      ELSE IF <artifact_or_action> is administrative record:
        SET <type> = <BureaucraticDecision>
      ELSE:
        SET <type> = <TraceCandidate>

    STEP 2: [locate-fixation
]
      FIND <inscription_mechanism> IN {
        writing,
        recording,
        archive,
        database,
        log,
        file,
        interface,
        policy,
        law,
        dataset,
        institutional-memory,
        public-circulation
}

      IF <inscription_mechanism> is absent:
        RETURN <not-yet-readable-as-public-trace>

    STEP 3: [produce-trace
]
      <event> [passes-away
]
      <the-said-or-done> [remains
]
      CREATE <Trace>

    STEP 4: [demote-intention
]
      SET <intention_status> = <evidence-not-sovereign>

      COMPARE:
        <known_intentions>
        <trace_structure>
        <actual_consequences>
        <circulation_history>
        <rival_readings>

      IF <known_intentions> contradict <trace_consequences>:
        MARK <meaning-exceeds-intention>

    STEP 5: [analyze-world-projection
]
      ASK:
        What <world> does this <Trace> open?
        What <roles> does it create?
        What <categories> does it stabilize?
        What <future-actions> does it enable?
        What <subjects> does it address?
        What <forms-of-life> does it make thinkable?

    STEP 6: [analyze-address
]
      MAP:
        <original_addressee>
        <unknown_reader>
        <institutional_reader>
        <machine_reader>
        <public_reader>
        <future_reader>

      SET <address_range> = all mapped readers

    STEP 7: [generate-guess
]
      BUILD <Guess> FROM:
        <trace_features>
        <origin_context>
        <inscription_mechanism>
        <consequences>
        <world_projection>
        <address_range>

      REQUIRE <Guess> to answer: "What does this trace mean now that it has escaped its origin?"

    STEP 8: [explain-structure
]
      MAP:
        <part> [relates-to
] <whole>
        <surface> [relates-to
] <deep-structure>
        <context> [relates-to
] <afterlife>
        <intention> [relates-to
] <consequence>
        <record> [relates-to
] <institution>
        <artifact> [relates-to
] <circulation>
        <category> [relates-to
] <power>

    STEP 9: [validate
]
      FOR EACH <RivalReading>:
        TEST:
          Does it explain more evidence?
          Does it better account for consequences?
          Does it expose hidden assumptions?
          Does it better map the world projected?
          Does it defeat the current guess?

      SELECT <best_reading> WHERE:
        <evidence_coverage> is strongest
        <structural_account> is strongest
        <consequence_account> is strongest
        <rival_defense> is strongest

      SET <validation_status> = <probable-not-final>

    STEP 10: [detect-failures
]
      IF <best_reading> depends only on intention:
        FLAG <NAIVE_INTENTIONALISM>

      IF <best_reading> reduces meaning to origin context:
        FLAG <CONTEXT_PRISON>

      IF <best_reading> treats all readings as equal:
        FLAG <INTERPRETIVE_NIHILISM>

      IF <best_reading> treats data as self-explaining:
        FLAG <DATA_POSITIVISM>

      IF <best_reading> treats procedure as neutral:
        FLAG <BUREAUCRATIC_INNOCENCE>

      IF <best_reading> treats AI artifact as single-author text:
        FLAG <AI_SINGLE_AUTHOR_FALLACY>

      IF <best_reading> treats archive as passive storage:
        FLAG <ARCHIVE_STORAGE_FALLACY>

    STEP 11: [return-report
]
      RETURN <HermeneuticReport> {
        trace_identity: <type>,
        fixation_mechanism: <inscription_mechanism>,
        detachment_analysis: <meaning-exceeds-intention>,
        world_projection: <world_projection>,
        addressee_range: <address_range>,
        interpretive_guess: <Guess>,
        explanation: <structure_map>,
        validation: <validation_status>,
        rival_reading_results: <rival_tests>,
        failure_flags: <flags>,
        final_reading: <best_reading>,
        remaining_uncertainties: <unresolved_questions>
}

  END PROGRAM


9. <Theory-Code Mapping>

  <types>
    <TraceInput> :=
      the empirical material submitted to interpretation.

    <Trace> :=
      the objectified remainder of speech, action, decision, media, or event.

    <HermeneuticReport> :=
      the disciplined reading of the trace after validation.

  </types>

  <functions>
    [classify-input
] :=
      distinguishes <speech>, <text>, <action>, <AI-artifact>, <bureaucratic-record>, and <historical-event>.

    [locate-fixation
] :=
      models Ricoeur's fixation of discourse and extension to action.

    [demote-intention
] :=
      prevents <author> or <agent> from becoming sovereign over meaning.

    [analyze-world-projection
] :=
      models the movement from <situation> to <world>.

    [generate-guess
] :=
      models the first movement of interpretation.

    [explain-structure
] :=
      models explanation internal to meaningful signs and traces.

    [validate
] :=
      models disciplined argument among probable readings.

    [detect-failures
] :=
      prevents the theory from collapsing into intentionalism, positivism, bureaucracy, or relativism.
  </functions>

  <classes>
    <HermeneuticTraceInterpreter> :=
      the whole conceptual machine.

    <InscriptionAnalyzer> :=
      the module that turns event into trace.

    <ValidationEngine> :=
      the module that turns guess into disciplined interpretation.

    <FailureDetector> :=
      the module that protects interpretation from false clarity.
  </classes>

  <tests>
    <test_trace_requires_fixation>
      GIVEN <event>
      WHEN no <inscription_mechanism> exists
      THEN return <not-yet-readable-as-public-trace>

    <test_intention_not_sovereign>
      GIVEN <known_intention>
      WHEN <trace_consequence> exceeds intention
      THEN mark <meaning-exceeds-intention>

    <test_rival_readings_required>
      GIVEN <Guess>
      WHEN no <RivalReading> is tested
      THEN flag <weak-validation>

    <test_ai_artifact_distributed>
      GIVEN <AIArtifact>
      THEN require {prompt, model, dataset, platform, circulation
}

    <test_bureaucratic_decision_as_interpretation>
      GIVEN <BureaucraticDecision>
      THEN classify <procedure> as possible <FrozenInterpretation>

    <test_archive_active>
      GIVEN <Archive>
      THEN analyze selection, organization, exclusion, and authorization
  </tests>

  <comments>
    // Meaning survives as trace, not as private intention.
// A record is not neutral; it is an action with an afterlife.
// A dataset is not raw memory; it is selected inscription.
// A bureaucratic category is a frozen reading.
// An AI artifact has distributed authorship.
// Validation is not final truth; it is disciplined comparative plausibility.
  </comments>

  <configuration>
    require_fixation: true
    intention_is_evidence_not_authority: true
    require_world_projection: true
    require_rival_readings: true
    require_failure_detection: true
    allow_multiple_probable_readings: true
    reject_all_readings_equal: true
    treat_archives_as_active: true
    treat_data_as_interpreted: true
    treat_bureaucracy_as_textual_action: true
    treat_ai_artifacts_as_distributed_traces: true
  </configuration>


10. <Residual Human Theory>

  <not-captured-by-program>
    The program can model <world-projection>, but it cannot feel the existential force of a world opening.
    The program can compare <rival-readings>, but it cannot guarantee ethical judgment.
    The program can expose <hidden-interpretation>, but it cannot decide alone what justice requires.
    The program can mark <meaning-exceeds-intention>, but it cannot absolve or condemn without human judgment.
  </not-captured-by-program>

  <future-maintainer-must-understand>
    This is not a neutral analysis pipeline.
    This is a hermeneutic discipline.

    The machine exists to stop weak interpretation from hiding behind:
      <authorial-intention>
      <agent-intention>
      <raw-data>
      <neutral-procedure>
      <technical-output>
      <archival-fact>
      <context-only-explanation>
      <single-author-theory>

    The maintained invariant is:
      <event> [vanishes
]
      <trace> [remains
]
